==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
Arabic {{ARchar|[[جهاد]]}} (ǧihād), '[[effort]]' or '[[struggle]]'.

===Pronunciation===<!-- not sure about stress and hence rhymes -->
*jĭ-häd, /dʒɪhɑːd/, /<tt>dZIhA:d</tt>/
*jə-häd', /dʒəˈhɑːd/, /<tt>dZ@"hA:d</tt>/

===Noun===
'''jihad'''

# {{Theology}} a [[personal]] [[spiritual]] [[struggle]] for [[self-improvement]] and against [[evil]]
# {{Islam}} A [[holy war]] undertaken by [[Muslim]]s for the purpose of ending [[oppression]].
#:''After the Prophet and his authorized Companian, no individual or group or state has the right to wage war against any non-Muslim country for the propogation of Islam.  Now '''Jihad''', or Qital to be precise, can be done by an Islamic state only for the pupose of ending oppression. -4:75 Q'uran''


